m/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_SAVED_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_SAVED_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_SAVED_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_SAVED_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>位于布里克斯顿的伦敦 O2 学院继去年因人群拥挤而关闭后，已获准保留其执照并重新开放。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li aria-level="1"><b>阅读更多：</b> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/artists-and-industry-speak-out-to-save-brixton-academy-itd-be-a-tragedy-to-lose-such-an-iconic-venue-3437059"><b>艺术家和业界大声呼吁拯救布里克斯顿学院：“失去这样一个标志性的场地将是一场悲剧”</b></a></li></ul><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hearing-into-the-future-of-brixton-academy-begins-a-venue-of-economic-and-cultural-importance-3496073">关于该场馆未来的听证会于周一（9 月 11 日）开始</a>，以确定学院音乐集团 (AMG) 是否可以继续在该音乐场馆运营其许可证，此前该音乐场馆因<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/four-asake-fans-in-critical-condition-after-disturbance-at-brixton-academy-gig-3367923">致命事故</a>而被迫关门。 2022 年 12 月<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/asake">Asake</a>音乐会上发生的<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/four-asake-fans-in-critical-condition-after-disturbance-at-brixton-academy-gig-3367923">人群拥挤事件</a>。</p><p>该事件<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/second-woman-dies-following-brixton-academy-incident-3369030">导致两人死亡</a>，一人伤势严重，最终导致学院的执照被吊销。 23 岁的加布里埃尔·哈钦森 (Gabrielle Hutchinson) 和 33 岁的丽贝卡·伊库梅洛 (Rebecca Ikumelo) 因而丧生。据报道，伦敦警察厅随后<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/o2-academy-brixton-faces-indefinite-closure-following-fatal-crowd-crush-3435471">敦促该地点永久关闭</a>。 </p><figure id="attachment_3498791" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3498791" style="width: 1667px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3498791" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_2.jpg" alt="布里克斯顿的一场 Asake 音乐会期间，人群拥挤，警方法医调查人员在布里克斯顿学院外看到。 （摄影：Thabo Jaiyesimi/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images）" width="1667" height="2500" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_2.jpg 1667w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_2-400x600.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_2-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_2-696x1044.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_2-1392x2088.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_2-1068x1602.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 1667px) 100vw, 1667px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3498791" class="wp-caption-text">布里克斯顿的一场 Asake 音乐会期间，人群拥挤，警方法医调查人员在布里克斯顿学院外看到。 （摄影：Thabo Jaiyesimi/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images）</figcaption></figure><p>现在，兰贝斯委员会今天（9 月 15 日星期五）宣布，学院可以重新开放，前提是它满足 77 项“旨在促进公共安全”的“广泛而有力”的条件。</p><p>潜在的重新开放日期尚未公布。 <em>NME</em>已联系学院音乐集团征求意见。</p><p> DJ 兼伦敦之夜沙皇艾米·拉梅 (Amy Lamé) 评论了这项裁决对布里克斯顿和首都音乐界的意义。</p><p>她在 X（前身为 Twitter）上写道：“首先，我的心与加比和丽贝卡的家人和亲人以及在 O2 布里克斯顿学院发生可怕事件后仍在医院中情况危急的妇女同在。”</p><p> “我知道 O2 Brixton 学院受到艺术家、歌迷和当地社区的重视，以及它对英国现场音乐界的重要性。我很高兴兰贝斯委员会对学院音乐集团能够安全地重新开放 O2 布里克斯顿学院感到满意。”</p><p>她补充道：“今天的决定是在详细审查证据和提出新计划之后做出的，这将确保去年的悲惨事件不再发生。”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">今天的决定是在详细审查证据和提出新计划之后做出的，这些计划将确保去年的悲惨事件不再发生。 3/3</p><p> — 艾米·拉梅 (@amylame) <a href="https://twitter.com/amylame/status/1702725460621230256?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 9 月 15 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>音乐场地信托基金还表示，他们“欢迎理事会重新开放学院的决定”，并将演出空间描述为“对当地社区、音乐迷以及更广泛的现场音乐生态系统具有巨大文化意义的空间”。</p><p> “我们期待为所有参与安全、成功重新启动这一标志性场馆的人员提供支持。</p><p>夜间产业协会首席执行官迈克尔·基尔对此表示同意，并表示这一决定标志着“保护这一珍贵地标的一个重要里程碑”。</p><p>基尔表示：“我们对在这个关键时刻团结在我们身后的无数支持者和利益相关者表示深深的谢意。”</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brixton-academy-refuse-racial-profiling-and-talk-ticketing-and-improving-safety-at-hearing-3496191"><strong>阅读更多：</strong>布里克斯顿学院拒绝种族定性和谈话票务以及提高听证会安全</a></li></ul><p>“布里克斯顿学院一直在音乐爱好者心中占有特殊的地位，其文化意义是不可估量的。我们一直主张其安全重新开放，今天的决定重申了我们坚定不移的承诺，即确保其作为现场音乐和娱乐中心的持续成功。”</p><p>他继续说道：“我们也认识到随之而来的重大责任，并承认去年 12 月发生的悲剧事件导致两人丧生。<br /> “我们坚决致力于支持实施商定的严格安全措施，以防止此类悲剧再次发生。我们最关心的仍然是所有享受夜生活的人的安全和享受。” </p><figure id="attachment_3498793" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3498793" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3498793" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_3.jpg" alt="布里克斯顿学院（摄影：Vuk Valcic/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images）" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_3.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_3-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_3-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_3-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_3-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_3-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3498793" class="wp-caption-text">布里克斯顿学院（摄影：Vuk Valcic/SOPA Images/LightRocket via Getty Images）</figcaption></figure><p>拯救我们的场景运动组织的乔治·弗莱明补充道：“布里克斯顿学院的未来受到保护，我们感到非常欣慰，许多其他学院也是如此。”</p><p> “我们认识到这是一起悲惨案件，并欢迎 AMG 和兰贝斯委员会实施的所有新安全措施。公众对这个场地的支持是巨大的，我们要感谢所有聚集在一起并签署各种请愿书和活动的人。”</p><p> Earlier this week, the sub-committee <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/hearing-into-the-future-of-brixton-academy-begins-a-venue-of-economic-and-cultural-importance-3496073">heard how Brixton Academy is “a venue of economic and cultural importance”,</a> with AMG arguing that “the Academy is not one of those venues on the police radar”.</p><p> “In 2022, the venue held 174 shows, 108 sell-outs,” said Philip Kolvin QC, speaking on behalf on AMG. “During the whole of that year, there was one police call for assistance. Every venue has to call the police from time-to-time.”</p><p> The hearing was then told of <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brixton-academy-refuse-racial-profiling-and-talk-ticketing-and-improving-safety-at-hearing-3496191">the venue&#39;s refusal of racial profiling and AMG&#39;S ambitious plans to improve ticketing and safety,</a> before things concluded with <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brixton-academy-hearing-lambeth-council-support-venue-reopening-in-principle-3496754">Lambeth Council saying that they supported the re-opening of Brixton Academy “in principle</a> ” if a series of conditions are met. The Met Police meanwhile, denied that they were looking to close the venue – but say that they believe current operator AMG “shouldn&#39;t be the licensee” if the Academy is to open its doors again.</p><p> Earlier this week saw Lambeth Council barrister Horatio Waller QC laid out conditions for the potential re-opening of the venue, while the Metropolitan Police stated their opposition to it opening its doors again under the stewardship of AMG.</p><p> Waller said that venue operator AMG have performed a “complete overhaul” of their security procedures and attitude towards risk assessments since the tragedy in December. These were, he continued, “independently audited” by consultants and commended as “comprehensive and robust”. Waller added that the results of these findings have given police “confidence to work with AMG to help develop their proposals further.”</p><p> Mr Kolvin QC also said that AMG are not “at loggerheads” with the Metropolitan Police, but he believes that the Police “view themselves [as] at loggerheads with us.</p><p> “The door is wholly open for when the Met Police choose to step through it,” he added, saying that AMG will give police “as much of an overview of the operation as they wish to have” and that they have “offered [police] a veto over events. They don&#39;t want it, but it was a symbol of my client&#39;s trust in the police.” </p><figure id="attachment_3498794" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3498794" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3498794" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_1.jpg" alt="Sub Focus perform on stage at Brixton Academy (Photo by Ollie Millington/Getty Images)" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_1.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_1-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_1-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_1-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/BRIXTON_ACADEMY_REOPENS_1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3498794" class="wp-caption-text"> Sub Focus perform on stage at Brixton Academy (Photo by Ollie Millington/Getty Images)</figcaption></figure><p> In response, Gerald Gouriet KC, legal counsel for the Met Police, dismissed reports in the media and online that the force want to see the O2 Academy Brixton shut permanently.</p><p> “The police do not wish to close the Academy,” he said in a closing argument. “I&#39;ve read again and again in the press and on social media that the police are trying to shut down the Academy permanently. That is simply not the case.”</p><p> Mr Kolvin QC also discussed suggested improved admittance procedures at Brixton Academy, and how gig-goers would be “removed rapidly” from the queue without the correct ticket if the venue were to re-open.</p><p> “There were some allegations made in this case, which may well be investigated by the SIA, that people were being allowed in by security without tickets,” said Mr Kolvin QC. “We don&#39;t have evidence that it was happening on the night, but we have [security operators] Showsec in – who are a different company – and now the ticketing is done by venue staff so my client has total control of the operation, using the new Safe Tix system developed by Ticketmaster, which is the most secure way of checking people in yet because it uses a revolving barcode.”</p><p> As well as the condition that “no one gets into the venue unticketed”, Mr Kolvin QC also explained how they had installed 16 new CCTV cameras outside the building and would be looking to increase the base number of medical staff at gigs, improving their radio communication between staff, having security with body-worn cameras, and strengthening the doors of the venue among other sweeping improvements regarding queuing and barriers.</p><p> Since the venue&#39;s closure in December, an <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/petition-launched-to-save-brixton-academy-3436989">online petition was launched</a> to counteract the closure <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/artists-and-industry-speak-out-to-save-brixton-academy-itd-be-a-tragedy-to-lose-such-an-iconic-venue-3437059">while various artists and industry professionals also spoke out against the potential shutting down of the venue</a> . So far it has attracted over 116,000 signatures.</p><p> Stuart O&#39;Brien, who started the petition, told this week&#39;s hearing: “We don&#39;t close sporting venues when tragedy strikes. What we do is take measures nationwide that keep everyone safe when attending those events. The same needs to happen here.</p><p> “It is not the building that is to blame for this tragedy, and providing the owner acts on the recommendations that are put to them, I&#39;m sure we can maintain a safe environment for everyone in the future.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/brixton-academy-allowed-to-retain-license-and-re-open-if-it-can-meet-robust-safety-rules-3498784">Brixton Academy allowed to retain licence and re-open if it can meet “robust” safety rules</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
